# Frontend Development Rules

## Technology Stack

- **Framework**: React 19 (functional components only)
- **UI Library**: Material UI (MUI) 7
- **Styling**: Emotion CSS-in-JS via MUI's styled API
- **State Management**: Zustand 5, Bacon.js for reactive streams
- **Routing**: React Router 7
- **Build Tool**: Vite 7
- **Date Handling**: Luxon
- **Validation**: Zod 4

## Project Structure

```
src/client/
├── App.tsx           # Root application component
├── data/             # State management, API, authentication
│   ├── ApiConnect.ts # Typed API client
│   ├── Login.ts      # Authentication state
│   └── State.ts      # Global state
├── ui/               # React components by feature
│   ├── category/     # Category management
│   ├── component/    # Shared/reusable components
│   ├── dialog/       # Modal dialogs
│   ├── expense/      # Expense CRUD and display
│   ├── general/      # Layout components
│   ├── grouping/     # Expense groupings
│   ├── hooks/        # Custom React hooks
│   ├── icons/        # Custom icons
│   ├── profile/      # User profile
│   ├── search/       # Search functionality
│   ├── shortcuts/    # Quick expense entry
│   ├── statistics/   # Charts and data viz
│   ├── subscriptions/ # Recurring expenses
│   └── tracking/     # Value tracking
└── util/             # Client-side utilities
```

## Component Pattern

Always use functional components with TypeScript:

```typescript
import * as React from 'react';
import { styled } from '@mui/material';

interface MyComponentProps {
  title: string;
  onAction: (id: number) => void;
  optional?: string;
}

export const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ title, onAction, optional }) => {
  const [state, setState] = React.useState<string>('');

  React.useEffect(() => {
    // Side effect logic
  }, [/* dependencies */]);

  const handleClick = React.useCallback(() => {
    onAction(123);
  }, [onAction]);

  return (
    <Container>
      <Title>{title}</Title>
      {optional && <Subtitle>{optional}</Subtitle>}
    </Container>
  );
};

const Container = styled('div')`
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 16px;
`;

const Title = styled('h2')`
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 1.25rem;
`;
```

## Styling

Use MUI's styled API with Emotion:

```typescript
import { styled } from '@mui/material';
import { colorScheme, primaryColors } from '../Colors';
import { media } from '../Styles';

const StyledCard = styled('div')`
  background-color: ${colorScheme.primary.light};
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 16px;

  ${media.mobile`
    padding: 8px;
  `}

  &.active {
    border: 2px solid ${primaryColors.dark};
  }

  &:hover {
    background-color: ${colorScheme.gray.light};
  }
`;
```

Use the responsive media helpers from `src/client/ui/Styles.ts`:
- `media.mobile` - Screens < 840px
- `media.mobilePortrait` - Screens < 600px
- `media.mobileLandscape` - Screens 600-839px
- `media.web` - Screens >= 600px
- `media.largeDevice` - Screens >= 1400px

