## Date Handling

Use Luxon for date manipulation:

```typescript
import { DateTime } from 'luxon';
import { toISODate, toDateTime, ISODate } from 'shared/time';

const today = DateTime.now();
const formatted = toISODate(today); // "2024-01-15"
const nextMonth = today.plus({ months: 1 });

// Use the toDateTime helper to convert various date inputs to DateTime
const date = toDateTime('2024-01-15'); // Returns DateTime

// Common operations
date.startOf('month');
date.endOf('year');
date.hasSame(otherDate, 'month');
date.toFormat('d.M.yyyy'); // "15.1.2024"
date.year; // 2024
date.month; // 1 (1-based, unlike Day.js which was 0-based)
date.weekNumber; // ISO week number
```

