## Dialog Pattern

Use the `UserPrompts` helper from `src/client/ui/dialog/DialogState.ts`:

```typescript
import { UserPrompts } from './dialog/DialogState';

const handleDelete = async () => {
  const confirmed = await UserPrompts.confirm(
    'Confirm Delete',
    'Are you sure you want to delete this item?'
  );
  if (confirmed) {
    // Perform delete action
  }
};

// For text input dialogs:
const handleRename = async () => {
  const newName = await UserPrompts.promptText(
    'Rename Item',
    'Enter new name:',
    currentName
  );
  if (newName) {
    // Use the new name
  }
};
```

## Table and List Patterns

For expense tables and lists, follow the patterns in `src/client/ui/expense/`:

```typescript
import { ExpenseTableLayout } from './row/ExpenseTableLayout';
import { ListDecorator } from '../component/ListDecorator';

// For tables
<ExpenseTableLayout>
  <thead><ExpenseHeader /></thead>
  <tbody>{items.map(renderItem)}</tbody>
</ExpenseTableLayout>

// For decorated lists with separators
<ListDecorator
  items={items}
  itemRenderer={ItemComponent}
  separator={SeparatorComponent}
  itemKey={item => String(item.id)}
/>
```

## Error Boundaries

Wrap components that may fail with error handling:

```typescript
import { ErrorView } from './general/ErrorView';

// In parent component
try {
  return <ChildComponent />;
} catch (error) {
  return <ErrorView title="Error" message={error.message} />;
}
```

## Logging

Use the client logger:

```typescript
import { logger } from 'client/Logger';

logger.info('Component mounted');
logger.warn({ context }, 'Warning message');
logger.error(error, 'Operation failed');
```

## File Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `ExpenseTable.tsx`, `CategoryPicker.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useAsyncData.ts`, `useWindowSize.ts`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `ClientUtil.ts`)
- Constants/Types: PascalCase (e.g., `Colors.ts`, `Types.ts`)

## Adding New Features

1. Create component files in the appropriate `ui/` subdirectory
2. Define any new types in `shared/types/` or `shared/expense/`
3. Add API methods to `client/data/ApiConnect.ts` if needed
4. Create custom hooks in `ui/hooks/` for reusable logic
5. Export components appropriately (named exports preferred)
